Lonnie Mayne https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lonnie_Mayne 0 Ronald Doyle "Lonnie" Mayne (September 12, 1944 – August 14, 1978) was an American professional wrestler in the 1960s and 1970s who frequently went by the name Moondog Mayne. Mayne wrestled in various NWA territories as well as the WWF. Lonnie was in an automobile accident on August 13, 1978, succumbing to his injuries on August 14,1978 at just 33 years old.
